[
    {
        "name": "<p><strong>NgRx and NgRx Workflow</strong></p>",
        "subjectId": 5,
        "sectionId": 48,
        "subSectionId": -1,
        "subSections": [
            {
                "name": "<p><strong>NgRx Flow</strong></p>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 48,
                "subSectionId": 49,
                "subSections": [],
                "contents": [
                    {
                        "description": "<p><strong>The NgRx Workflow:</strong></p></br><p><strong>1. Component Interaction: </strong>A user interaction or an <strong>event </strong>in a <strong>component </strong>triggers the <strong>dispatch of an Action</strong>.</p></br><p><strong>2. Action Dispatch: </strong>The component <strong>dispatches an action</strong> to the <strong>Store</strong>.</p></br><p><strong>3. Reducer Update:</strong>The <strong>Reducer </strong>receives the <strong>action </strong>and the <strong>current state</strong>, and based on the <strong>action type</strong>, it calculates and returns a <strong>new state</strong>. The <strong>Store </strong>then updates its <strong>state </strong>with this <strong>new value</strong>.</p></br><p><strong>4.</strong> <strong>Effect Handling (Optional):</strong> If the <strong>dispatched action </strong>requires a <strong>side effect</strong> (e.g., an API call), an <strong>Effect </strong>listens for that <strong>action</strong>. The <strong>Effect </strong>performs the <strong>asynchronous operation </strong>and, upon completion, <strong>dispatches a new action</strong> (e.g., <code class=\"ql-font-monospace\" style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(229, 237, 255);\">LoadMoviesSuccess</code><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> or </span><code class=\"ql-font-monospace\" style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(229, 237, 255);\">LoadMoviesFailure</code> <span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">). This </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">new action</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> is then processed by a </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Reducer</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></p></br><p><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">5. Selector Subscription:</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Components </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">subscribe to specific parts of the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">state </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">using </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Selectors</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></p></br><p><strong>6. View Update:</strong> When the state in the Store changes, the selectors notify the subscribing components, which then re-render to reflect the updated data.</p></br><p><strong>Flow Diagram (simplified)</strong></p><pre data-language=\"plain\">\n[Component] --dispatch--&gt; [Action] \n    |                           |\n    v                           v\n[Effect] --async tasks--&gt; [Action Success/Failure] --&gt; [Reducer] --&gt; [Store updated]\n    ^\n    |\n[Selectors] &lt;--component subscribes-- \n</pre>",
                        "subjectId": 5,
                        "sectionId": 48,
                        "subSectionId": 49,
                        "contentId": 136,
                        "text": "<p>Can you explain NgRx Flow (Redux Pattern in Angular)?</p>"
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
        "contents": [
            {
                "description": "<p><strong>NgRx</strong> in <strong>Angular</strong> is a <strong>state management library</strong> built on top of <strong>RxJS</strong> (<em>Reactive Extensions for JavaScript</em>).</p></br><p> It helps manage and maintain the <strong>application state</strong> in a <strong>predictable</strong> (easy to understand and debug) and <strong>scalable</strong> (grow with your application without becoming messy) way, especially useful in <strong>large Angular applications</strong> where multiple components interact with <strong>shared data</strong>.</p></br><p>It follows the <strong>Redux pattern</strong> (<strong>single store</strong>, <strong>unidirectional data flow</strong>, <strong>immutability</strong>), but implemented with <strong>Angular</strong> and <strong>RxJS</strong>.</p></br><p>It uses <strong>Actions</strong>, <strong>Reducers</strong>, <strong>Selectors</strong>, and <strong>Effects</strong> to manage and handle <strong>application state</strong> and <strong>side effects</strong> like <strong>API calls</strong>.</p>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 48,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 137,
                "text": "<p>What is NgRx in Angular?</p>"
            },
            {
                "description": "<p><strong>NgRx</strong> handles <strong>immutability</strong> by using <strong>pure functions</strong> (<strong>reducers</strong>) that return <strong>new state objects</strong> instead of modifying the <strong>existing state</strong> directly.</p>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 48,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 138,
                "text": "<p>How does NgRx handle immutability?</p>"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "name": "<p><strong>key concept of NgRx (Store, Actions, Reducer, Selectors, effects)</strong></p>",
        "subjectId": 5,
        "sectionId": 50,
        "subSectionId": -1,
        "subSections": [],
        "contents": [
            {
                "description": "<p>The <strong>Store</strong> in <strong>NgRx</strong> is a <strong>centralized state management container</strong> for Angular applications. It holds the entire <strong>application state</strong> in a <strong>single tree structure</strong>, following the <strong>Redux pattern</strong> and <strong>RxJS observables</strong>.</p></br><ul><li><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(10, 10, 10);\">The single source of truth for the application state.</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(10, 10, 10);\">Holds the entire application state tree.</span></li><li><span style=\"background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); color: rgb(10, 10, 10);\">Provides methods to dispatch actions and select data.</span></li></ul></br>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 50,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 139,
                "text": "<p>What is ‘store’ in NgRx?</p>"
            },
            {
                "description": "<p><strong>Actions</strong> are <strong>plain TypeScript objects</strong>, and they are the <strong>only way</strong> to express that <strong>something happened</strong> (e.g., a <strong>user clicked a button</strong>, <strong>data loaded</strong> from an <strong>API</strong>, or a <strong>login failed</strong>).</p>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 50,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 140,
                "text": "<p>What is ‘Actions’ in NgRx?</p>"
            },
            {
                "description": "<ul><li><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Are </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">pure functions </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">responsible for updating the application state based on </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">dispatched actions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Receive the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">current state</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> and an </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">action as input</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Return a new </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">state object</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, ensuring immutability of the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">original state</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Define how the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">state changes</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> in response to </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">specific actions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li></ul>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 50,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 141,
                "text": "<p>What is ‘Reducer’ in NgRx?</p>"
            },
            {
                "description": "<ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Pure functions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> used to extract specific </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">pieces of data</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> from the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">store</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li><li><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Allow </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">components </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">to subscribe to only the relevant parts of the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">state</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">optimizing performance</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> and preventing unnecessary</span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> re-renders</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li></ul>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 50,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 142,
                "text": "<p>What is ‘Selectors’ in NgRx?</p>"
            },
            {
                "description": "<ul><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Handle side effects</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, which are </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">asynchronous operations</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> or </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">interactions </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">with external resources (e.g., API calls, local storage).</span></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Listen </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">for specific </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">actions </strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">and perform </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">asynchronous tasks</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li><li><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">Dispatch new actions</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"> (e.g., success or error actions) upon completion of the </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">side effect</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">, which are then handled by </span><strong style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">reducers</strong><span style=\"color: rgb(10, 10, 10); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">.</span></li></ul><p class=\"ql-indent-1\"></p>",
                "subjectId": 5,
                "sectionId": 50,
                "subSectionId": -1,
                "contentId": 143,
                "text": "<p>What are ‘effects’ in NgRx?</p>"
            }
        ]
    },
