            {
                "name": "<p><strong>createSelector and createFeatureSelector</strong></p>",
                "sectionId": 116,
                "subSectionId": 117,
                "subjectId": 5,
                "contents": [
                    {
                        "text": "<p>Difference between <code>createSelector</code> and <code>createFeatureSelector</code> in NgRx</p>",
                        "sectionId": 116,
                        "subSectionId": 117,
                        "subjectId": 5,
                        "contentId": 405,
                        "description": "<p><strong>createFeatureSelector:</strong></p><p>Used to select a <em>top-level feature slice</em> from the global store.</p></br><p><strong>How it works:</strong></p><ul><li>It takes the feature key.</li><li>Returns the whole feature state object.</li><li>Acts as the starting point for more specific selectors.</li></ul></br><pre data-language=\"plain\">\nexport const selectEmployeeFeature =\n  createFeatureSelector&lt;EmployeeState&gt;(&#39;employees&#39;);\n</pre></br><p><strong>createSelector:</strong></p><p>Used to derive a <strong>specific piece</strong> of data from the <strong>feature state</strong>  or <strong>another selector</strong> or <strong>multiple selectors</strong></p></br><pre data-language=\"plain\">\nexport const selectEmployees = createSelector(\n  selectEmployeeFeature,\n  (state) =&gt; state.employees\n);\n</pre>"
                    }
                ],
                "subSections": []
            }
        ]
    }
